product_name: MACPowder Kiss Liquid Lipcolor Longwear Lipstick
summary: SummaryMAC Powder Kiss Liquid Lipcolor is a long-wearing liquid lipstick with a whipped, mousse-like texture and blurred, high-impact matte lip color. Moisturizing liquid lipstick formula delivers ten hours of moisture-matte, comfortable, hydrating lip color.
details: DetailsBenefitsSmoothing, hydrating moisture-matte liquid lipstickJust the right amount of high-impact lip colorImmediate and 10-hour moistureLong-wearing, 10 hoursSmooth, stay-true lip color, 10 hoursSoft-focus and blurred lipstick color effectFade-resistant, non-settling, non-creasing, and non-flakingKey IngredientsBlend of Vitamin E, Powders and Emollient Properties: Provide excellent cushion, flexibility, wear and moisture that will leave lips looking and feeling soft and smooth all dayResearch ResultsConsumer testing on 116 women after one week:95% said it applied smoothly onto lips94% said it left lips feeling soft and smooth upon application92% said it was colour-true throughout wear91% said it left lips feeling moisturized upon applicationItem 2635503How To UseApply liquid lipstick directly to lips as desired with the hourglass-shaped lip color applicator that perfectly hugs lips to fill in lines and enhance lips with a smoothing and blurring effect.IngredientsDimethicone, Dimethicone Crosspolymer, Isononyl Isononanoate, Polyglyceryl-2 Triisostearate, Diisostearyl Malate, Tribehenin, Tocopheryl Acetate, Lecithin, Ethylhexyl Palmitate, Isopropyl Myristate, Polyglyceryl-3 Polyricinoleate, Polyglyceryl-2 Diisostearate, Sorbitan Isostearate, Dehydroacetic Acid, Isostearic Acid, Polyhydroxystearic Acid, Vanillin, [+/- Mica, Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891), Iron Oxides (CI 77491), Iron Oxides (CI 77492), Iron Oxides (CI 77499), Blue 1 Lake (CI 42090), Red 6 (CI 15850), Red 7 (CI 15850), Red 22 Lake (CI 45380), Red 28 Lake (CI 45410), Red 33 Lake (CI 17200), Yellow 5 Lake (CI 19140), Yellow 6 Lake (CI 15985)].Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details
how_to_use: Apply liquid lipstick directly to lips as desired with the hourglass-shaped lip color applicator that perfectly hugs lips to fill in lines and enhance lips with a smoothing and blurring effect.

reviews.headline: Powder Lipstick
reviews.comments: This lipstick is okay I didn't realize that it's the powder one, but I'll keep it this time, but will pay close attention next time and not get it.

reviews.headline: Very nice.
reviews.comments: You don't need to use a lot. Goes on better with a q tip. Lasts a long time and doesn't dry out lips.

reviews.headline: Love color
reviews.comments: Love the color and it feels silky on. Doesn't last longer than some drug store brands and the price is outrageous for how many times you need to reapply throughout the day. Wouldn't buy again for $30 that's insane.

reviews.headline: Very disappointed
reviews.comments: I always loved this brand, however this line is horrendous. It's dry, looks horrible, won't last a week if I wore it. Waste of $$$

reviews.headline: Super Smooth
reviews.comments: Super smooth but gets on teeth. Double check before going out!

reviews.headline: I like this a lot
reviews.comments:
Most matte is very drying and I unfortunately get that dry layer of lip skin that can just....peel. I usually have to stick to moisturizing lipsticks. Although not very moisturizing, this is moisturizing enough that I can enjoy matte. 

Make it Fashun is very pretty, I think I will also get Billion $ Smile. This might be my new go-to for the year.

reviews.headline: My new fav lippie!
reviews.comments: I love you so much. I have never used these before, but they are so creamy and the colors are so beautiful. They wear so comfortably and last a long time.

reviews.headline: so buttery smooth
reviews.comments: As a cool tone girlie I've been eyeing at the shade It's Personal for months now and I finally caved in and bought it. The formula is so buttery and moisturising. Reminds me of the old nyx matte lip creams. You will definitely need to reapply if you eat or drink, but I don't mind it because it's a beautiful color and feel. I love to pair this with Makeup Forever Endless Cacao, Nyx Touch Up Taupe, or Mob Beauty M159.

reviews.headline: Better than the regular lipsticks
reviews.comments: I loved this lipstick so much I want all the colors and hope MAC will bring more colors from the original lipsticks. I have problems getting all the color onto my lips with the regular lipstick, this covered all of my lips with literally one swipe! Buying more colors! lasts a good bit slightly fades when drinking but not like normal lipstick.

reviews.headline: One of my go to lipsticks
reviews.comments: The color was great. I love Mac powder kiss because it lasts almost all day while at work. I work with the public so it is good to not have to go and reapply so often.

reviews.headline: So comfy on the lips!
reviews.comments: Love this formula, I almost forget im even wearing any lipstick.

reviews.headline: Literally Obsessed

reviews.headline: Favorite Lippie

reviews.headline: Good
reviews.comments:
I personally love Mac lipsticks and this one does not disappoint. I like the over the taupe. I buy so many lip
sticks, but I never finish them before buying another one, but I actually ran this one dry so that says a lot.

reviews.headline: I love this this product
reviews.comments: The color is beautiful and it lasts all day

reviews.headline: I get the hype but unfortunately not for me
reviews.comments: I bought this since i was interested in a more nudey cool tone shade and unfortunately it didnt do well with my light neutral/olive skintone. Regarding the feel, i found it a little drying and kinda patchy. Could just be me but sadly it didnt work out.

reviews.headline: comfortable
reviews.comments: I purchased Buffiest and It's Personal. Both apply slightly sheer, but application is very smooth w/o patches. While I do not find them moisturizing, they do not dry out my lips and comfortable on. They wear more like bullet lipsticks than traditional liquid lipsticks, and are not exactly long-lasting.

reviews.headline: I'll buy this product again.

faceoff_positive.comments: To say I love these would be The Understatement of the Year. The PKLLs are dense mousse lipsticks that can provide everything from a soft blurred wash of color to a more opaque, stronger effect. You can create a sharp edge with the wand applicator or diffuse with a lip brush, your finger, or just by smushing your lips together. One coat will dry down slightly, preventing excessive transfer. Two or more coats will leave a softer balmy feeling, but with more chances to transfer and pill as the day wears on. These will also smear a bit if you are wearing your mask for an hour+. I have extremely wrinkly lips and these do not settle, crack or crease. However, they also do not leave much of a stain behind. I didn't find the online swatches helpful at all. I bought 3 "blind" (MACSMASH, Devoted to Chili, and A Little Tamed), loved them so much I bought 3 more (Over the Taupe, Make Love to the Camera, and the More the Mehr-ier) and loved all 6 of them SO MUCH I literally just ordered every single other color on the Ulta website because they are just $15 during the Black Friday sale. The photos were all taken in natural light. I have light/medium skin with both yellow and red undertones  for reference I can wear most foundations running NC20 to NW35 (I'm mixed race european and asian). Of course, YMMV and everyone has their own preferences regarding color, texture, scent, longevity, etc. but I really think most people will like these, as they are just the perfect liquid, bullet, powder hybrid. And if you liked but were somewhat underwhelmed by the original bullet Powder Kiss Lipsticks, and enjoyed the Pony Effect Limited edition mousse lipsticks even tho they don't last long, you will LOVE the PKLLs because they blow both the bullets and Pony out of the water in terms of performance, comfort, and color-saturation.
faceoff_positive.headline: You will love these!

faceoff_negative.comments: I had SUCH high hopes for this when I initially tried it on! I purchased Date-Maker (because you can't try on in stores currently) and instantly fell in love when I tried it on in my car. It has an extremely light and soft weight. The color is BEAUTIFUL... a perfect warm nude that I have been searching for forever... (I typically wear Hitch Hiker or Uptight in the Urban Decay comfort mattes, but I've been on the hunt for a liquid lipstick that could survive wearing masks). However, by the time I got home from my 20 minute drive... the color disappeared! I thought maybe I didn't apply enough. The next day, I did full makeup and applied this... only to find it disappeared an hour later! So. I want to love it. I DID love it... but it frankly doesn't last longer than an average chapstick. If there is a trick to get this to last... lipliner or lipgloss or anything... I would try to purchase again. As of now, I returned it. If there is a long lasting lipstick in this same color, I would love to purchase it!!!
faceoff_negative.headline: I am SO bummed
